# Python Package Management with uv

Use uv exclusively for Python dependency management and execution.

- Manage dependencies via `pyproject.toml` + `uv.lock`; do not use pip/poetry/pip-tools/conda.
- Add/remove packages: `uv add <package>`, `uv remove <package>`.
- Sync environments from lockfile: `uv sync`.
- Run tools and scripts with `uv run`, e.g. `uv run pytest`, `uv run ruff`, `uv run python -m app.cli.summary --url <URL>`.
